<img src="Images\PokyDex.png"> : Hello! I'm your Pokedex! Welcome to PokeTwine!

<img src="Images\PokyDex.png"> :  This is a huge open world game, with a ton of different activities and fun stuff. Ask me about anything, then we can get going!

[[The Field]]
[[Cities]]
[[Quests]]
[[Pokemon->Pokemon Tutorial]]
[[100% List]]

[[START]]


:: PC {"position":"1200,1775","size":"100,100"}
You turn on the PC.

...pokemon.transfer.sytem = ONLINE

Welcome to the Transfer Sytem! Please select a Pokemon from the box to place in your party!

BOX
(for: each _mon, ...$box)[(link:_mon's Species)[(set:$SelectedItem to _mon)(go-to:"BoxSwitching")]<br>]

[[Back->PalletAshInside2]]


:: Pallet Town Decoration {"position":"100,900","size":"100,100"}
A trinket you bought in Pallet Town. Might look good in your room.

(link-goto:"Back", $MenuReturn)


:: PalletAsh {"position":"1300,1425","size":"100,100"}
IN FRONT OF YOUR HOUSE

You are standing in front of your small cottage. Its walls are white-painted wood planks, and it has a red tile roof. Around you, nothing but grass, fields and a river for a few hundred meters. To the east, a dirt path that goes through some plantations. To the north, a path to the center of the town. You can go inside the house. There is a sign here.

[[East->PalletField]]
[[North->PalletCenter]]
[[Read sign->PalletAshSign]]
[[Go inside->PalletAshInside1]]

[[Menu]]

(set:$Location to "PalletAsh")


:: PalletAshInside1 {"position":"1200,1425","size":"100,100"}
INSIDE YOUR HOUSE

You step inside your house. As soon as you step inside, your mom gives you a big hug. You're standing in the spacious living room. A TV is put up against the wall opposite to the door, and there's a staircase on the right-side wall. You can exit the house, go up the stairs or talk to your mom.

[[Exit the house->PalletAsh]]
[[Go up the stairs->PalletAshInside2]]
[[Talk to mom->PalletAshInsideMom]]

[[Menu]]

(set:$Location to "PalletAshInside1")


:: PalletAshInside2 {"position":"1200,1525","size":"100,100"}
INSIDE YOUR HOUSE

You go up the wooden stairs and head to your bedroom instinctively. You step inside. Your bunkbed and pokemon plushies haven't moved since you left. If you got any cool items from your travels, this is a great spot to drop them off. Or you can go back to the living room. You can also use your PC.

[[ACTIVITY #1: Bedroom Decoration]]
[[Use PC->PC]]
[[Go back downstairs->PalletAshInside1]]

[[Menu]]

(set:$Location to "PalletAshInside2")


:: PalletAshInsideMom {"position":"1100,1425","size":"100,100"}
You talk to your mom.

MOM: Hello my little pumkin! You look tired. You shouldn't overwork yourself you know... 

Want to rest?
[[Yes->PalletAshInsideMom1]]
[[No->PalletAshInside1]]


:: PalletAshInsideMom1 {"position":"1100,1525","size":"100,100"}
You and your pokemon rest a while...

HP MAXED

[[Back->PalletAshInside1]]

(set:$Party's 1's hp to (floor:((($PKindex's ($Party's 1's Species)'s Stats's 1)*$Party's 1's lv)/50)+10))]

(if:  (length of $Party) > 1)[(set:$Party's 2's hp to (floor:((($PKindex's ($Party's 2's Species)'s Stats's 1)*$Party's 2's lv)/50)+10))]

(if:  (length of $Party) > 2)[(set:$Party's 3's hp to (floor:((($PKindex's ($Party's 3's Species)'s Stats's 1)*$Party's 3's lv)/50)+10))]

(if:  (length of $Party) > 3)[(set:$Party's 4's hp to (floor:((($PKindex's ($Party's 4's Species)'s Stats's 1)*$Party's 4's lv)/50)+10))]

(if:  (length of $Party) > 4)[(set:$Party's 5's hp to (floor:((($PKindex's ($Party's 5's Species)'s Stats's 1)*$Party's 5's lv)/50)+10))]

(if:  (length of $Party) > 5)[(set:$Party's 6's hp to (floor:((($PKindex's ($Party's 6's Species)'s Stats's 1)*$Party's 6's lv)/50)+10))]


:: PalletAshSign {"position":"1300,1525","size":"100,100"}
You look at the wooden sign on a pole.

(text-colour:grey)[NORTH PATH]: PALLET TOWN
(text-colour:grey)[EAST PATH]: FIELDS, GARY'S HOUSE

[[Back->PalletAsh]]


:: PalletCenter {"position":"1300,1300","size":"100,100"}
TOWN CENTER

You reach a (relatively) dense part of Pallet Town. You're standing in the main plaza. A few rustic buildings circle you.  From where you are, you see a PokeMart, a Souvenir Shop and a Farming Shop. To the west, the river is flowing slowly as always. A small bridge lets go get across and to Prof. Oak's lab on the other side. To the south, you can take a dirt path to your house. Finally, the road to Viridian City lies to the north.

[[PokeMart->PalletCenterPokeMart]]
[[Souvenir Shop->PalletCenterSouv]]
[[Farming Shop->PalletCenterFarm]]
[[West->PalletOak]]
[[South->PalletAsh]]
[[North->Route 1-1]]

[[Menu]]

(set:$Location to "PalletCenter")


:: PalletCenterFarm {"position":"1525,1175","size":"100,100"}
PALLET TOWN FARMING SHOP

You enter the farming shop. You never really got into farming, despite the surroundings of your house being almost only farmland. So no real reason to by anything here for yourself.

(if:$Qindex's Q1 is "Step 1")[ [[Farming Equipment (Q1)->Q1-2]] ]

[[Back->PalletCenter]]


:: PalletCenterPokeMart {"position":"1400,1300","size":"100,100"}
PALLET TOWN POKEMART

You enter the PokeMart. Preparing before an adventure is always a good idea.

Gold: $Gold

(link:"Pokeball, 20g")[(if:$Gold >=20)[(set:$PokeballCount to it +1)(set:$Gold to it - 20)](else:)[(print:" Not enough money")]]

(link:"Potion, 50g")[(if:$Gold >=50)[(set:$PotionCount to it +1)(set:$Gold to it - 50)](else:)[(print:" Not enough money")]]

[[Back->PalletCenter]]


:: PalletCenterSouv {"position":"1500,1300","size":"100,100"}
PALLET TOWN SOUVENIR SHOP

You step inside the souvenir shop. Since you live here, no real reason to "souvenir" it, but you can never have enough useless trinkets to put in your room.

Gold: $Gold

(set:_it to "Pallet Town Decoration")(unless:$Inventory contains _it or $BedroomSlot1 is _it or $BedroomSlot2 is _it or $BedroomSlot3 is _it)[(link:"Pallet Town Decoration, 50g")[(if:$Gold >=50)[(set:$Inventory to it + (a:"Pallet Town Decoration"))(set:$Gold to it - 50)](else:)[(print:" Not enough money")]]]

[[Back->PalletCenter]]


:: PalletField {"position":"1425,1425","size":"100,100"}
FIELDS OF PALLET TOWN

You're walking along a dirt path, going through some labored fields of wheat. At the end of the path to the east, you spot Gary's house. To the west, you can go to your home. (if:$Qindex's Q1 is "Unstarted")[Also, you spot a farmer who seems to have trouble with his plantation.] You let (print:$Party's 1's Species) out to walk with you, and it's walking alongside you.

(print:$Party's 1's png) : (print:$PKindex's ($Party's 1's Species)'s Cry)

[[East->PalletGary]]
[[West->PalletAsh]]
(if:$Qindex's Q1 is "Step 2")[[[Return to farmer->Q1-3]]<br>](if:$Qindex's Q1 is "Unstarted")[[[Go talk to the farmer->PalletFieldFarmer]]<br>]
[[Menu]]

(set:$Location to "PalletField")


:: PalletFieldFarmer {"position":"1425,1525","size":"100,100"}
You walk up to the farmer.

''QUEST #1: Farming Equipment''
FARMER: Oh hey Ash. Could you go into the village and fetch some new farming equipment? A Snorlax fell asleep on my old one yesterday, and when he left they were completely crushed. I'll cover the cost and pay you for it. What do you say?

[[Begin quest->Q1-1]]
[[Back->PalletField]]



:: PalletGary {"position":"1550,1425","size":"100,100"}
GARY'S HOUSE

You don't have the keys, so you can't enter. It's a house shockingly similar to yours, but with a blue roof instead of a red one. You can go west back into the fields, nothing else to do actually.

[[West->PalletField]]

[[Menu]]

(set:$Location to "PalletGary")


:: PalletOak {"position":"900,1300","size":"100,100"}
As you approach Oak's lab, you hear him shout to you from atop the hill.

OAK: HEY ASH! The developer was too lazy to make this part. Come back later!

[[Back->PalletCenter]]


